bug.short_desc: Youtube video visible if another window opened

assigned_to.name: Nobody; OK to take it and work on it

long_desc.thetext:
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 5.1; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0 Build Identifier: Firefox/4.0
In firefox 4, if we are playing a youtube video, then the video is visible in another open window.
Pre-requisites: Firefox 4 opened with another window, say notepad.
Reproducible: Sometimes
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Open any youtube video. 2. After some time (1-2 minutes), open notepad window. Actual Results: The youtube video is visible on top left corner of notepad.
Expected Results: The video should not be playing in any other windows.
The bug is not re-producible each time. Sometimes when we open any other window after the video starts playing, the video is visible. But, in some cases, you may need to switch between firefox and notepad 3-4 times.
Created attachment 524629 Screenshot showing youtube video visible in notepad

Is your Issue reproducible when you disable the Hardware Acceleration and restart Firefox? If yes, please post the Content of the Graphics Section you can get via "about:support" after you re-enabled Hardware Acceleration.

Created attachment 525048 Graphics section from about:support
The issue is reproducible when I disable the Hardware Acceleration and restart Firefox.
I have attached graphics section screenshot from about:support.

Could you please check out if a Driver Update would help? http://downloadcenter.intel.com/
Does a Flash Plugin Update help? http://www.adobe.com/go/getflash/
